details: The script utilizes the OAR (Open Application Resource) batch system for resource allocation. It requests a single node with one GPU, a wall time of 12 hours, and specifies the project "pr-cg4n6". The script also uses the conda environment "CGDetection" and runs a Python script named "main.py" located within the "CGvsNI-SSL/src" directory. The Python script appears to train a model on the CIFAR10 dataset using Temporal Ensembling.
